    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-11-07T17:26:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-11-07T17:26:00-05:00" n="392"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/11–752: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d392fn1">Drafted and signed by the Director of the Office of
                        International Administration and Conferences (<persName
                            corresp="#p_INGRAMGM1">Ingram</persName>). Cleared in the Bureau of
                            <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Affairs (<persName
                            corresp="#p_HICKERSONJD1">Hickerson</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_SANDIFERDV1">Sandifer</persName>).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-11-07T17:26:00-05:00"
                            >November 7, 1952—5:26 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40. For <persName corresp="#p_HALLWO1">Hall</persName>. <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> concerned over reports <gloss target="#t_LADels1"
                        >LADels</gloss> pressing for turnover Contributions Comite terms of ref and
                    substitution straight natl income formula. This obviously attempt capitalize on
                    current domestic political situation. <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>,
                    in discussions <gloss target="#t_LAs1">LA</gloss> and other <gloss
                        target="#t_Del1">Del</gloss>s <pb facs="0639" n="611" xml:id="pg_611"/> and
                    as required in formal statements <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> sessions,
                    shld point out in strongest terms that one-third goal US contribution <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>, first set under leadership late Senator
                        <persName>Vandenburg</persName>, represents inflexible unity of opinion both
                    parties. Must do everything possible make other <gloss target="#t_Del1"
                        >del</gloss>s understand foreseeable reaction of incoming administration on
                    being faced with rebuff to US on this crucial issue. Cld have greatest effect on
                    US public opinion and cld substantially condition attitude new administration
                    toward fon aid generally and individual country proposals. If <gloss
                        target="#t_LADels1">LADels</gloss> continue maintain their concern is effect
                    on own dollar contributions, on supposition wld be impossible burden <gloss
                        target="#t_Sov1">Sov</gloss> and satellite states with full impact US
                    reduction one-third, offer to join with them in reducing budget to level which
                    wld permit reduction US to one-third without requiring monetary increase their
                    contribution 1953. Except insofar as modified by requirements this strategy,
                        <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> authorizes <gloss target="#t_Del1"
                        >del</gloss> to support <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> move 5th Comite
                    for first reading decision on gross expenditure budget of $48,700,000.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
